To use the Monaspace Neon font in your Zed editor config, you'll need to add it to your `settings.json` file. Here's how to specify it:

```json
{
  "ui.font_family": "Monaspace Neon"
}
```

If you want to set it specifically for the editor text, you can use:

```json
{
  "editor.font_family": "Monaspace Neon"
}
```

If the font name contains spaces and you want to be extra safe, you can also write it with quotes:

```json
{
  "editor.font_family": "'Monaspace Neon'"
}
```

Make sure the font is properly installed on your system for this to work. You can verify the exact font name in your system's font settings if it's not working with these settings.
